Few of Us (Lithuanian: Mūsų nedaug) is a 1996 Lithuanian drama film directed by Šarūnas Bartas. It was screened in the Un Certain Regard section at the 1996 Cannes Film Festival.[1] The film shows a young woman visiting a nomadic Tofalar tribe in the Sayan Mountains.[1] There is no dialogue throughout the film.[2]
